    <h2 id="whyIs">Why is watering important?</h2>
    
    <p>Watering a plant is very important for its growth. Plant's use a process called photosynthesis to create energy and water is required for it to work.</p>
    <br>
    <p>Photosynthesis uses carbon dioxide from the air and hydrogen from the water to create a type of sugar that can be used by the plant to grow. </p>
    <br>
    <br>
    <p>Water carries nutrients like the sugar from the leaves to the stems and buds, supporting new growth.</p>
    <br>
    <p>Water helps the plant stay cool by evaporating water in the leaves and taking away excess heat, this also pulls up more water from the ground.</p>
    <br>
    <p>Water provides support to the plant cells and allows it to bend in the wind without breaking.</p>
    <br>
    <p>Without water a plant will start to brown and eventually die.</p>
