    <h2 id="tips">Tips for a healthy garden</h2>
    <p>Give the soil time to dry, letting the soil dry slightly makes the plant reach deeper into the ground and creates healthy roots.</p>
    <br>
    <br>
    <p>Water in the evening or early morning, watering while the soil is cool lets the plant absorb more of the moisture before it evaporates.</p>
    <br>
    <br>
    <p>Keep your plant leaves dry, this helps avoid various diseases.</p>
    <br>
    <br>
    <p>Water evenly and gradually. Make sure that the plant is getting an even amount of water from all sides, this helps promote even root growth. Watering gradually allows time for the water to seep into the soil and avoids runoff, try watering in parts.</p>
    <br>
    <br>
    <p>Avoid overwatering, if too much water is left in the soil it can drown the roots of the plant. Make sure your plants have good drainage so the roots can breathe.</p>
  
